            comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4555-3795")))
Maintainer: Luigi Colin <luigi.colin@uni-konstanz.de>
Description: Shiny tools to process CBASS-derived PAM data efficiently. Minimal requirements are PAM-based photosynthetic efficiency data (or data from any other continuous variable that changes with temperature, e.g. relative bleaching scores) from 4 coral samples (nubbins) subjected to 4 temperature profiles of at least 2 colonies from 1 coral species from 1 site. Please refer to the following CBASS (Coral Bleaching Automated Stress System) papers for in-depth information regarding CBASS acute thermal stress assays, experimental design considerations, and ED5/ED50/ED95 thermal parameters: Nicolas R. Evensen et al. (2023) <doi:10.1002/lom3.10555> Christian R. Voolstra et al. (2020) <doi:10.1111/gcb.15148> Christian R. Voolstra et al. (2025) <doi:10.1146/annurev-marine-032223-024511>.
